🚨BREAKING: Scientists Raise Alarm For 'Quad-Demic' In Another Plandemic Fear-Mongering Campaign To Control The Population And Harm Trump Administration

Here we go again. The headlines scream "quad-demic," and mainstream media is working overtime to whip us into a frenzy. 

Flu, COVID-19, RSV, and norovirus are apparently teaming up like some viral Avengers to terrorize America this winter. But this is just another plandemic narrative designed to control us 

The So-Called "Quad-Demic"

Reports claim the U.S. is facing a simultaneous surge of four viruses:

Flu: 3.1 million cases so far, with 37,000 hospitalizations and 1,500 deaths.

COVID-19: 2.5 to 4.4 million cases since October, along with thousands of hospitalizations and deaths.

RSV: Hospitalizations are up 40% in just two weeks, affecting tens of thousands.

Norovirus: The highest outbreak levels for this time of year since 2012, allegedly fueled by contaminated raw oysters.

Sounds terrifying, right? But let’s take a closer look at what’s really going on.

Mask Mandates Are Back—But Why?

As if we haven’t been through enough, hospitals in states like Wisconsin, California, and New Jersey are already reintroducing mask mandates. 

Officials in New York City are urging masks on public transport. Remember when we were promised "two weeks to flatten the curve"? Fast forward to today, and it seems like masks are making a permanent comeback.

But here's the kicker: These mandates are being reinstated despite a lack of concrete evidence that masks prevent the spread of respiratory viruses on a large scale. 

The timing feels suspiciously convenient as fear of the "quad-demic" grows.

The Convenient Surge in Numbers

The rise in cases is being attributed to holiday travel, increased social gatherings, and weakened immune systems. 

Let’s not forget that many of these "surges" are based on estimates, not hard data. For example:

COVID-19 case numbers are presented in ranges as wide as 2.5 to 4.4 million.

Norovirus outbreaks have "tripled," but how much testing is actually happening?

This vagueness raises a critical question: Are we dealing with an actual public health crisis, or is this another case of manipulated stats to justify more restrictions?

Fear-Based Control Tactics

It’s no coincidence that the narrative of weakened immune systems from lockdowns and work-from-home policies is being pushed hard. 

Blame the people for following the very measures that "experts" insisted would save lives. Now, they want us to get multiple vaccines, wear masks again, and stay inside—sound familiar?

The Real Agenda?

This isn’t the first time we’ve been told to fear invisible enemies. The original COVID-19 pandemic saw unprecedented government overreach, from lockdowns to vaccine mandates. And now, with the quad-demic, it feels like déjà vu. Are these viruses real? Sure. But is the panic justified? That’s another story.

The flu, COVID-19, RSV, and norovirus have been around for decades. Yet suddenly, we’re told they’re teaming up in some kind of viral conspiracy? The timing is just too perfect to be a coincidence. Is this about public health, or is it about maintaining control?

"The bottom line that everybody needs to be aware of, of course, the CDC doesn't have much credibility these days. So here's the key things that people need to keep in mind that I'm empowering you, the audience."

"So here's the way that any professional ought to be looking at any emerging infectious disease outbreak. Two key points to consider. Number 1, are you seeing a high level of death in hospitalization on a per case basis? In other words, what's the case fatality rate?"

"Is it high or is it low? And the second thing that you need to look for is whether or not there's evidence of sustained human to human transmission. That is pure unadulterated fear porn. What it represents is a artifact of data sampling."

quotedStatus.text:
Dr. Peter McCullough: "The current strain of bird flu is a product of gain of function research done in the USDA Poultry Research Laboratory in Athens, Georgia. So it is a man made problem that, our farms are experiencing right now. It's in the peer reviewed literature, and, I mean, it's really you know, the next steps in this outbreak is, for people to understand, you know, the ramifications of it personally and how to be prepared."

"It's the circulating clade, which is the kind of the original source strain, is clade 2.3.4.4b, and, again, that is a product of what's called serial passage gain of function research done at the USDA Poultry Research Laboratory." 

"It was assisted, by University of Wisconsin School of Veterinary Medicine and, Rotterdam University. The gain of function was to get it to spread from chickens into migratory waterfowl or mallard ducks. And so that's how it's spreading across the world now."

"It's been spreading for 4 years. It continually reinfects the farms because the mallard ducks fly around, and they land in in ponds on farms and they, easily infect the other animals, on the farm. So it was able to, in a sense, expand the host range even into cattle and to sea mammals." 

"Now the good news is it's much milder than bird flu of decades ago, and then there's the peer reviewed paper by Nick Hulscher on this. And, you know, and this has not been denied by the USDA Poultry Research Center."

"McCullough Foundation attended the bird flu summits in both, University of Arkansas as well as in Washington, DC. So there's no denial of this. Just like COVID 19, the bird flu problem is a man made problem by the US government."

text:
🚨BREAKING: Bird Flu Panic Is Another Big Pharma Hoax— Here’s Why You Should Be Skeptical

Another “deadly virus” headline is here, and this time it’s about bird flu (H5N1). 

The media and Big Pharma want you to believe we’re on the brink of a pandemic, but let’s break it down. 

Are we really facing the next global crisis, or is this just another manufactured scare to line the pockets of the vaccine industry? 

Spoiler: It’s looking like a hoax.

So, the first severe U.S. case of bird flu was reported in Louisiana. Health officials found “concerning mutations” in the virus. Sounds scary, right? But dig a little deeper, and it’s not what they’re hyping it up to be.

These mutations supposedly help the virus “adapt” to humans, but here’s the catch: They happened late in the infection, and they’re super rare. Translation? The virus is still mostly a bird problem. Yet the fear machine is running full steam ahead.

The real agenda here? Keep you afraid. Scientists are talking about how bird flu and seasonal flu could “swap genes” to create a super-virus. But let’s get real—how often does that actually happen?

Virologist Angela Rasmussen warned, “It’s only a matter of time before it spreads like seasonal flu.” Yeah, we’ve heard this before—remember swine flu? SARS? Monkeypox? All hyped to the max, with no apocalypse in sight.

Here’s where things get interesting. The CDC says we already have candidate vaccines for H5N1. But instead of rolling them out, they’re dangling the idea like a carrot. Why? To prep you for another cash-grab vaccine campaign.

Dr. Rasmussen is already calling for farmworkers to be vaccinated. But why inject people with a rushed vaccine for a virus that isn’t even spreading among humans? It’s the same playbook we’ve seen before: create fear, push vaccines, rake in billions.

Let’s not forget who wins when panic spreads:

•Big Pharma cashes in on vaccine contracts.

•Governments tighten control through emergency declarations.

•Media profits from clicks and fearmongering.

Meanwhile, regular folks are left paying more for eggs and living in unnecessary fear.

We’ve been here before. They overhype the danger, push the vaccine, and then quietly move on when the profits are made. Don’t let them fool you again.

Question everything, stay informed, and most importantly, don’t let Big Pharma use fear to control your life.

Bird flu is just the latest boogeyman in their endless cycle of scare tactics. Don’t buy the hype—and definitely don’t buy the vaccine.

These mutations supposedly help the virus “adapt” to humans, but here’s the catch: They happened late in the infection, and they’re super rare. Translation? The virus is still mostly a bird problem. Yet the fear machine is running full steam ahead.

The real agenda here? Keep you afraid. Scientists are talking about how bird flu and seasonal flu could “swap genes” to create a super-virus. But let’s get real—how often does that actually happen?

Virologist Angela Rasmussen warned, “It’s only a matter of time before it spreads like seasonal flu.” Yeah, we’ve heard this before—remember swine flu? SARS? Monkeypox? All hyped to the max, with no apocalypse in sight.

Here’s where things get interesting. The CDC says we already have candidate vaccines for H5N1. But instead of rolling them out, they’re dangling the idea like a carrot. Why? To prep you for another cash-grab vaccine campaign.

Dr. Rasmussen is already calling for farmworkers to be vaccinated. But why inject people with a rushed vaccine for a virus that isn’t even spreading among humans? It’s the same playbook we’ve seen before: create fear, push vaccines, rake in billions.

Let’s not forget who wins when panic spreads:

•Big Pharma cashes in on vaccine contracts.

•Governments tighten control through emergency declarations.

•Media profits from clicks and fearmongering.

Meanwhile, regular folks are left paying more for eggs and living in unnecessary fear.

We’ve been here before. They overhype the danger, push the vaccine, and then quietly move on when the profits are made. Don’t let them fool you again.

Question everything, stay informed, and most importantly, don’t let Big Pharma use fear to control your life.

Bird flu is just the latest boogeyman in their endless cycle of scare tactics. Don’t buy the hype—and definitely don’t buy the vaccine.

quotedStatus.name: Mario Nawfal
quotedStatus.text:
🚨🇺🇸 ARE THE GAETZ ALLEGATIONS PART OF A WITCH HUNT AGAINST TRUMP’S LOYALISTS?

In February 2023, the DOJ closed a sex trafficking investigation into Matt Gaetz without filing any charges, despite years of scrutiny. 

Gaetz’s attorneys confirmed that the probe, which began in 2020, ended with no legal action.

Fast forward to late 2024, when Rep. Gaetz resigned from Congress after Trump nominated him for Attorney General in November. 

Trump’s decision to appoint Gaetz, citing his dedication to ending “weaponized government,” reignited political opposition and scrutiny of Gaetz’s past. 

Facing fierce backlash, Gaetz withdrew his nomination on November 21 to avoid a contentious confirmation process and allow Trump’s administration to focus on “Day 1 readiness.”

But now, the House Ethics Committee report that was released yesterday accuses Gaetz of paying for sex with a 17-year-old girl and using drugs, citing payments totaling $90,000 to multiple women. 

The timing has raised questions: if the DOJ couldn’t build a case after a 3-year investigation that ended without charges, why are these allegations surfacing so strongly after Gaetz’s nomination by Trump?

Gaetz denies the allegations:

“These claims are completely false. I have never paid for sex, nor engaged in illegal drug use. This is a smear campaign.”

Notably, Christopher Dorworth, named in the report, has demanded retractions for what his legal counsel calls “demonstrably false” claims.

According to Dorworth’s lawyer:

1.There’s no evidence Gaetz invited anyone to Dorworth’s home.

2.Dorworth was never confronted with cell phone records as alleged.

3.Dorworth’s legal team provided exculpatory evidence that the report ignored.

Dorworth’s lawyer accused the Committee of making absurd assumptions:

“This report should be retracted immediately.”

If the DOJ couldn’t substantiate these claims with years of investigation, are these allegations credible—or politically motivated retaliation for Trump’s nomination of @Mattgaetz?

Sources: NY Post, Reuters, PNJ, Vox, NY Magazine

🚨 BOMBSHELL Photos Expose Biden Family’s Long Denied China Connections

These newly uncovered images, obtained through litigation with the National Archives and Records Administration (NARA), paint a startling picture of then-Vice President Biden’s close ties to Hunter Biden’s Chinese business associates and high-ranking officials in the Chinese government—including none other than President Xi Jinping himself.

Here’s what these explosive photos show:

•Joe Biden and Xi Jinping Chumming It Up: Then-VP Biden appears to introduce his son, Hunter, to Chinese President Xi Jinping during a 2013 official trip to Beijing.

•Cozy with Chinese Vice President Li Yuanchao: Biden also introduced Hunter to Li Yuanchao, another high-ranking official in China.

•Business Meets Politics: Photos reveal Biden meeting Hunter’s business associates at BHR Partners, including CEO Jonathan Li and Managing Partner Ming Xue.

These aren’t just casual meet-and-greets; they align perfectly with the House Oversight Committee’s findings that Hunter leveraged his father’s political influence to secure deals and VIP access in China.

This scandal almost didn’t see the light of day. NARA had planned to release the photos on October 23, 2024—just weeks before the election. But Biden and Obama’s legal teams swooped in, invoking a 30-day extension to keep these images hidden until after Election Day. Coincidence? You decide.

The timing couldn’t be more suspicious. During Joe Biden’s official Asia trip, Hunter tagged along, and it wasn’t for sightseeing. Biden reportedly introduced his son to Chinese officials and business tycoons while in Beijing. One of these associates, Jonathan Li, even gained preferential access to then-U.S. Ambassador Max Baucus as part of Hunter’s BHR deal—a condition that screams political privilege.

But wait, there’s more. Joe Biden didn’t stop at introductions. According to Hunter’s former business partner, Devon Archer, and emails found on Hunter’s infamous laptop, Biden wrote letters of recommendation for Jonathan Li’s children. That’s right—the sitting Vice President was penning glowing recommendations for the offspring of his son’s business associate.

Here’s the kicker: The Biden-Harris Administration is still withholding 182 of the 313 photographs processed by NARA. What’s in those other photos that they don’t want us to see? AFL is fighting to find out, but the mere fact that these images exist raises serious questions about the extent of the Biden family’s dealings.

Michael Ding, counsel for America First Legal, didn’t mince words:

“Every day, more evidence comes out showing how the Biden family leveraged Joe Biden’s long career in public office for private gain. America First Legal will not stop fighting to uncover the full story of the Biden Family’s corruption.”

This isn’t just another political scandal—it’s a potential smoking gun. As Biden pardons his son for alleged past crimes and his administration buries evidence, these photos offer a glimpse into a web of influence that stretches all the way to the Chinese government.
